This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves training a deep learning model to predict diabetic macular edema grades from fundus photographs. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could place it in the medical imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the analysis of visual data.
